(C, D).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C370650EFFDFFFC8FF1CF893BE5DC88B" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="234" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFDFFFC9FF1CF893BDB1C723" blockId="12.[136,1452,1179,2086]" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FF1CF893BFCAC89E" bold="true" box="[189,255,1918,1944]" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">Note:</emphasis>
—Only one species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FE44F892BD52C89E" box="[485,615,1918,1944]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FE44F892BD52C89E" box="[485,615,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">P. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, alternating between 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FCF4F893BCA5C89E" box="[853,912,1918,1944]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Violaceae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FCF4F893BCA5C89E" box="[853,912,1918,1944]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">Viola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FC65F892BB32C89F" box="[964,1031,1919,1945]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FC65F892BB32C89F" box="[964,1031,1919,1945]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">Carex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been reported (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDFFFC9FB7EF893BFF7C8BA" author="Ono, Y. &amp; Kakishima, M." pageId="12" pageNumber="233" pagination="1543 - 1546" refId="ref21036" refString="Ono, Y. &amp; Kakishima, M. (1981) Puccinia pulchella: a new Viola-Carex rust from Japan. Canadian Journal of Botany 59: 1543 - 1546." type="journal article" year="1981">Ono &amp; Kakishima 1981</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDFFFC9FF6EF84CBEF4C8BA" author="Hiratsuka, N. &amp; Sato, S. &amp; Katsuya, K. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. &amp; Kaneko, S. &amp; Ono, Y. &amp; Sato, T. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K." box="[207,449,1953,1980]" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" refId="ref19488" refString="Hiratsuka, N., Sato, S., Katsuya, K., Kakishima, M., Hiratsuka, Y., Kaneko, S., Ono, Y., Sato, T., Harada, Y., Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K. (1992) The rust flora of Japan. Tsukuba-shuppankai, Tsukuba, Japan." type="book" year="1992">
Hiratsuka 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FEE5F84FBE43C8BD" box="[324,374,1953,1979]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
). However, teliospore size of this species (37.5–56.0 × 13.5–20.5 µm) is larger than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FF07F828BE1CC8D9" box="[166,297,1989,2015]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FF07F828BE1CC8D9" box="[166,297,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">P. pulchella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(27–47 × 11–19 µm). Teliospores of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FD69F828BC48C8D9" box="[712,893,1989,2015]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-violae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FD69F828BC48C8D9" box="[712,893,1989,2015]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">P. caricis-violae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are morphologically similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDFFFC9FA9AF828BE6DC704" authority="Homma" authorityName="Homma" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricissadoensis">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FA9AF828BFC0C704" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">P. caricissadoensis</emphasis>
Homma
</taxonomicName>
reported in 
<collectingCountry id="F37D7615FFDFFFC9FE46F805BD12C704" box="[487,551,2024,2050]" name="Japan" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDFFFC9FD99F805BDA8C705" author="Ito, S." box="[568,669,2024,2051]" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" refId="ref19696" refString="Ito, S. (1950) Mycological flora of Japan, vol. 2, no. 3. Yokendo, Tokyo, Japan." type="book" year="1950">Ito 1950</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDFFFC9FD0BF805BC95C704" author="Hiratsuka, N. &amp; Sato, S. &amp; Katsuya, K. &amp; Kakishima, M. &amp; Hiratsuka, Y. &amp; Kaneko, S. &amp; Ono, Y. &amp; Sato, T. &amp; Harada, Y. &amp; Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K." box="[682,928,2024,2050]" pageId="12" pageNumber="233" refId="ref19488" refString="Hiratsuka, N., Sato, S., Katsuya, K., Kakishima, M., Hiratsuka, Y., Kaneko, S., Ono, Y., Sato, T., Harada, Y., Hiratsuka, T. &amp; Nakayama, K. (1992) The rust flora of Japan. Tsukuba-shuppankai, Tsukuba, Japan." type="book" year="1992">
Hiratsuka 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDFFFC9FC80F804BC61C704" box="[801,852,2024,2050]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="233">et al</emphasis>
. 1992
</bibRefCitation>
). However, because of the lack of a uredinial stage, this species is treated as a new species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF15660DFFDEFFC8FF29F997BA52C9FA" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6416765" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6416765" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6416765/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" startId="13.[136,229,1658,1680]" targetBox="[151,1436,191,1633]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFDEFFC8FF29F997BA52C9FA" blockId="13.[136,1452,1658,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FF29F997BE35C989" bold="true" box="[136,256,1658,1680]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDEFFC8FEA9F996BEDFC989" box="[264,490,1658,1680]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caricis-violae">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FEA9F996BEDFC989" box="[264,490,1658,1680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Puccinia caricis-violae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDEFFC8FDB2F997BD87C996" box="[531,690,1658,1680]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Violaceae" genus="Viola" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acuminata">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FDB2F997BD87C996" box="[531,690,1658,1680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Viola acuminata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FD62F997BDC6C996" bold="true" box="[707,755,1658,1680]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">A–G</emphasis>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDEFFC8FC8EF996BCB8C996" box="[815,909,1659,1680]" class="Liliopsida" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Carex" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FC8EF996BC5CC996" box="[815,873,1659,1680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Carex</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FC3CF996BC85C996" bold="true" box="[925,944,1659,1680]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">H</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FC1FF996BCF2C996" bold="true" box="[958,967,1659,1680]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">I</emphasis>
). 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FC7FF997BCDAC989" bold="true" box="[990,1007,1658,1679]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">A</emphasis>
. Plants producing spermogonia and aecia on the leaf surface in the field. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FE38F972BE9CC9B2" bold="true" box="[409,425,1695,1716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">B</emphasis>
. Aecia on the lower leaf surface. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FD50F973BC37C9B2" bold="true" box="[753,770,1694,1716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">C</emphasis>
. Vertical section of a spermogonium. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FBD5F972BBB0C9B2" bold="true" box="[1140,1157,1695,1716]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">D</emphasis>
. Vertical section of an aecium surrounded with peridia. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FED6F92EBEB2C9DE" bold="true" box="[375,391,1731,1752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">E</emphasis>
. Aeciospores. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FDB5F92EBD16C9DE" bold="true" box="[532,547,1731,1752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">F</emphasis>
. An aecium observed under SEM. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FCCFF92FBCB4C9DE" bold="true" box="[878,897,1730,1752]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">G</emphasis>
. Aeciospores with granules on the surface observed under SEM. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FF64F90ABFEDC9FA" bold="true" box="[197,216,1767,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">H</emphasis>
. Telia on the leaf surface. 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FE77F90ABEEAC9FA" bold="true" box="[470,479,1767,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">I</emphasis>
. Vertical section of a telium. Scale bars: 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FCC9F90BBC98C9FA" bold="true" box="[872,941,1766,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">C, E, J</emphasis>
= 20 μm, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FBB1F90ABB14C9FA" bold="true" box="[1040,1057,1767,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">D</emphasis>
= 30 μm, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FB24F90ABBA1C9FA" bold="true" box="[1157,1172,1767,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">F</emphasis>
= 50 μm, 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FB57F90BBA3CC9FA" bold="true" box="[1270,1289,1766,1788]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">G</emphasis>
= 10 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BD53685FFDEFFC8FF1CF8C1BE5DC88B" blockId="13.[136,1452,1835,1933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDEFFC8FF1CF8C1BD60C843" authority="Ono &amp; Kakish." authorityName="Ono &amp; Kakish." box="[189,597,1835,1861]" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FF1CF8C1BEA0C843" box="[189,405,1835,1861]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Puccinia pulchella</emphasis>
Ono &amp; Kakish.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDEFFC8FDC9F8C6BCB3C843" author="Ono, Y. &amp; Kakishima, M." box="[616,902,1835,1861]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" pagination="1543 - 1546" refId="ref21036" refString="Ono, Y. &amp; Kakishima, M. (1981) Puccinia pulchella: a new Viola-Carex rust from Japan. Canadian Journal of Botany 59: 1543 - 1546." type="journal article" year="1981">Ono &amp; Kakishima 1981</bibRefCitation>
) is an illegitimate later homonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6A4D06FFDEFFC8FAE9F8C1BE48C86F" authority="Peck (1873)" authorityName="Peck" authorityYear="1873" class="Pucciniomycetes" family="Pucciniaceae" genus="Puccinia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Pucciniales" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pulchella">
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FAE9F8C1BFC5C86F" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">Puccinia pulchella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDEFFC8FF57F8A2BE48C86F" author="Peck, C. H." box="[246,381,1871,1897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" pagination="41 - 72" refId="ref21118" refString="Peck, C. H. (1873) Descriptions of new species of fungi. Bulletin of the Buffalo Society of Natural Sciences 1: 41 - 72." type="journal article" year="1873">Peck (1873)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
under ICN Shenzhen Code Art 53.1 (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFB4B74FFDEFFC8FCBAF8A2BCC1C86F" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[795,1012,1871,1897]" pageId="13" pageNumber="234" refId="ref21616" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="B91EEA97FFDEFFC8FCDAF8BDBC87C86F" box="[891,946,1871,1897]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="234">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
), therefore, a replacement name for this species is proposed.
